           SPELL=fcrontabs
         VERSION=1.1
       BUILD_API=2
      LICENSE[0]=PD
         ENTERED=20030714
         UPDATED=20030714
        KEYWORDS="utils"
           SHORT="directories to put commands in to run regularly."
cat << EOF
The fcrontabs spell installs directories such as /etc/cron.daily where
other spells can drop executables to be run at intervals. Since it
uses fcron, you can tell it to run /etc/cron.daily at the same time
every day or every 24 hours the computer is up by editing /etc/fcrontab.
EOF
